            <h3>VENUS</h3>
            <p>
             Venus is the second planet from the Sun. It is named after the Roman goddess of love and beauty. As the second-brightest natural object in the 
             night sky after the Moon, Venus can cast shadows and, rarely, is visible to the naked eye in broad daylight.Venus lies within Earth's orbit, and so never appears to venture far from the Sun,
              setting in the west just after dusk and rising in the east a bit before dawn. Venus orbits the Sun every 224.7 Earth days
            </p>
