            <p>
              Mars is the fourth planet from the Sun and the second-smallest planet in the Solar System after Mercury. In English, Mars carries a name of the
               Roman god of war and is often referred to as the 'Red Planet'.The latter refers to the effect of the iron oxide prevalent on Mars' surface, which gives it a
               reddish appearance distinctive among the astronomical bodies visible to the naked eye
            </p>
