            <p>
              Neptune is the eighth and farthest known planet from the Sun in the Solar System. In the Solar System, it is the fourth-largest 
              planet by diameter, the third-most-massive planet, and the densest giant planet. Neptune is 17 times the mass of Earth, slightly more massive
               than its near-twin Uranus. 
              Neptune is denser and physically smaller than Uranus because its greater mass causes more gravitational compression of its atmosphere. 
            </p>
